<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16895] RemoteCopyLagSegments metric taking active segment into account</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16895</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The RemoteCopyLagSegment is off by 1 because it also includes the active segment into account while the RemoteCopyLagBytes does substract the size of active segment: &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; bytesLag = log.onlyLocalLogSegmentsSize() - log.activeSegment().size();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; topic = topicIdPartition.topic();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; partition = topicIdPartition.partition();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; segmentsLag = log.onlyLocalLogSegmentsCount();
brokerTopicStats.recordRemoteCopyLagBytes(topic, partition, bytesLag);
brokerTopicStats.recordRemoteCopyLagSegments(topic, partition, segmentsLag);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
